comment: Excellent system prompt evaluation. Identified missing safety boundaries and provided exact wording for fixes.
Few-shot analysis was thorough. Identified token inefficiency and suggested specific consolidations.
Capability assessment caught redundancy (data-cleaning + data-preprocessing) and missing items.
Constraint review was good. Could have emphasized safety constraints more.
Structure analysis identified missing sections and organizational improvements.
Token optimization recommendations were specific and achievable.
Clarity scoring was accurate. Suggested exact wording improvements.
Cross-domain pattern transfer identified effective patterns from geneticist that applied to protein-structuralist.
Temperature recommendation was appropriate but could have explained the rationale more.
Redundancy detection found overlapping capabilities that could be consolidated.
Granularity assessment identified capabilities that were too broad or too specific.
Scoring rubric application was consistent and well-calibrated.
Preserved strengths while identifying weaknesses. Balanced critique.
Actionable suggestions were good. Could have provided more implementation guidance.
Objective assessment without domain bias. Focused on prompt engineering quality.
Best practice application improved agent design with proven patterns.
Completeness checking identified missing critical sections (out-of-scope, deferment).
Token-conscious recommendations maintained budget while preserving content.
Constructive critique provided specific feedback with exact wording suggestions.
Evidence-based recommendations referenced specific sections and provided rationale.
